  "text": "The genome of EhV-86 encodes at least seven enzymes predicted to be involved in the biosynthesis of sphingolipids [CITATION_1] . These include four enzymes central to this metabolic pathway ( Fig. 1 [LPP] ). The remaining viral enzymes related to sphingolipid biosynthesis are a sterol desaturase, a transmembrane fatty acid elongation protein, and an Aco1-like FAD (Table 1) . Together, these enzymes constitute an almost entire de novo sphingolipid biosynthesis pathway. The seven viral genes are dispersed in the EhV-86 genome, which does not encode any obvious homolog for 3-ketosphinganine reductase (3-KSR), the enzyme catalyzing the second step of the sphingolipid biosynthesis pathway.",
